page.title: 14HEDGEROW SURVEY.
page.content: {Hedgerow Survey June 24th 1985} Location _ Road at entrance to Trayne Farm drive.The hedge is a stone and earth bank 1.14m high and 1m thick topped with a hedge which is kept closely cut.The grass verge is 1.70m wide. {Flowers in bloom: Wall Pennywart,Buttercup,Dock, Dandelion,Rape,Cowparsley - 2 types, Foxglove,Crack Willow,Cuckoo Pint, Common Storksbill,Red Campion. {Other Plants: Ivy,Stinging Nettles,Harts Tongue, Moss,Bracken. {Trees and Bushes: } Brambles,Sycamore,Elder,Honeysuckle, Beech,Hawthorn. {Grasses: Tall Fescue,Tuffed Hair,Bearded Couch, Cocksfoot,Couch.
